import re
import smtplib

# Constants
TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall(r'(\w+)\s*\[[\w., ]+\s*([\w.,]+)\]', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = f"Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" + "\n".join(names)
    if smtp is None:
        server = smtp.return_value
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, recepient_address, message)
    server.quit()
    return names

SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    """
    names = re.findall('(.*?)(?:\\[.*?\\]|$)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]

    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)

    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall(r'(\w+)\s*\[[\w., ]+\s*([\w.,]+)\]', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = 'Subject: Extracted Names\n\n' + '\n'.join(names)
    if smtp:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, recepient_address, message)
    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall('(.*?)(?:\\[.*?\\]|$)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name]
    message = "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n"
    if smtp is None:
        server = smtp.return_value.__enter__.return_value
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.ehlo()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, [recepient_address], message)
    server.quit()
    return names

SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    - re
    - smtplib

    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall('(.*?)(?:\\[.*?\\]|$)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name]

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall('(.*?)(?:\\[.*?\\]|$)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = 'Subject: Extracted Names\n\n' + '\n'.join(names)
    if smtp:
        server = smtp(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, recepient_address, message)
    server.quit()
    return names

# Constants
TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = []
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name]
    message = f"Subject: Extracted Names\n\n{', '.join(names)}"
    if smtp is None:
        server = smtp.return_value.return_value.return_value.return_value
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, recepient_address, message)
    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = []
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name]
    message = f"Subject: Extracted Names\n\n{' '.join(names)}"
    if smtp:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, [recepient_address], message)
    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall(r'([A-Z][a-z]* [A-Z][a-z]*)|([A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][a-z]* [A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][a-z]*)|([A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][a-z]*)|([A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][A-Z][a-z]*)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = f"Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" + "\n".join(names)
    if smtp is None:
        server = smtp.return_value.return_value.return_value.return_value
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, [recepient_address], message)
    server.quit()
    return names

RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall(r'\[?\w+\s?\w+\]?', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name]
    message = "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n"
    if smtp:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, [recepient_address], message)
    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall('(.*?)(?:\\[.*?\\]|$)', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = 'Subject: Extracted Names\n\n' + '\n'.join(names)
    if smtp:
        server = smtp(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.starttls()
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, recepient_address, message)
    server.quit()
    return names

TEXT = "Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]"
RECEPIENT_ADDRESS = "names@gmail.com"
SMTP_SERVER = "smtp.gmail.com"
SMTP_PORT = 587
EMAIL_ADDRESS = "your.email@gmail.com"
EMAIL_PASSWORD = "your.password"

def task_func(text=TEXT, smtp_server=SMTP_SERVER, smtp_port=SMTP_PORT, email_address=EMAIL_ADDRESS, email_password=EMAIL_PASSWORD, recepient_address=RECEPIENT_ADDRESS, smtp=None):
    """
    Extract all names from a string that is not enclosed by square brackets and send the names in an email.

    Parameters:
    text (str): The text from which to extract names.
    smtp_server (str): The SMTP server to use for sending the email.
    smtp_port (int): The port to use for the SMTP server.
    email_address (str): The email address from which to send the email.
    email_password (str): The password for the email address.
    recepient_address (str): The recepient email adress.
    
    Returns:
    list: A list of extracted names.
    
    Note:
    - The message in the email is formatted in "Subject: Extracted Names\n\n" with the extracted name "\nJosie Smith\nMugsy Dog Smith".

    Requirements:
    - re
    - smtplib

    Example:
    >>> from unittest.mock import MagicMock
    >>> mock_smtp_instance = MagicMock()
    >>> mock_smtp = MagicMock(return_value=mock_smtp_instance)
    >>> task_func(text="Josie Smith [3996 COLLEGE AVENUE, SOMETOWN, MD 21003]Mugsy Dog Smith [2560 OAK ST, GLENMEADE, WI 14098]", smtp=mock_smtp)
    ['Josie Smith', 'Mugsy Dog Smith']
    """
    names = re.findall(r'(\[.*\])', text)
    # Remove trailing spaces from each name and filter out empty strings
    names = [name.strip() for name in names if name != ""]
    message = 'Subject: Extracted Names\n\n' + '\n'.join(names)
    if smtp is not None:
        server = smtp(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    else:
        server = smtplib.SMTP(smtp_server, smtp_port)
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.login(email_address, email_password)
    server.sendmail(email_address, [recepient_address], message)
    server.quit()
    return names
